Package: parseTweetFiles
Version: 0.8
Title: Parse Tweet Files
Description: All code necessary to convert tweet files downloaded by the StreamR package to a usable format. Can tag tweets with zip codes, filter variables, filter by time zone, remove all strange symbols from tweets, and convert them into a character array. Can also fit topic models to a set of timestamped Tweets.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Author: Robert Turner <rwturner@wisc.edu>
Maintainer: Robert Turner <rwturner@wisc.edu>
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown
Imports: dplyr, sp, maptools, maptpx, LDAvis, tm
Depends: R (>= 2.10)
LazyData: true
VignetteBuilder: knitr
